annotation.TEXT: Okay, so this bottom row of levels is done, and I think this is a good place to end the episode.

Success! So, yeah. This is one of those levels where you have to defeat all of the enemies to win. Once they're all gone, the level is cleared (oh, and you won't automatically walk to the right during these level clears, so don't worry about that).
Huh. The overworld music disappeared. It also disappeared after completing that Rumia level earlier, too. Well, whatever. Level 7 is next.
Sanae demos: 2
Nuts. No Cirnos. Just more precision swimming with random bullets. Hopefully Sanae won't get ambushed at a bad time!
BGM: Super Mario All-Stars - Title Screen
Alright, so here's the world map. As you can see, there's a whole ton of levels here, and you can basically move around at warp speed, which is nice!

Ooh, lots of cannons. Looks tricky, but once again, this actually isn't too bad. Just be aware that the only true safe spots here are your starting position, and the rope platform (and once you reach the rope platform, you're practically done).
Oh, boy. It's one of Bear's favorite levels! See that firebreathing Rumia over there? The goal here is to drop her into the lava. This one is very tricky!
Think fast!
The jump from the second-last fence to the last fence here is the trickiest.

Well, this looks kind of tricky, maybe. Also, note that these fences actually act like vines. That may not seem significant, but vines are easier to grab the edges of than fences, which is important here.
Okay, time for level 9. Maybe there are also Cirnos in this level?
Be ready to dodge soon after starting this level!
Something something! Something something something... Yep, this is a whole lot of something.
Oh, and since this level ended with a goal sphere, you don't have to defeat every enemy, so don't worry if you end up leaving something behind you alive.
Each of these levels is a short single-screen challenge. Also, you start with 99 lives, which you might very well need, given how tricky these challenges can get.
BGM: Kid Icarus NES - Sky Palace
Sanae demos: 1
BGM: Princess Tomato in the Salad Kingdom - Level 8 - Castle
Whoops, somehow hit Start by accident, but yeah, you can look around the map this way, not that you'd need to.

Aside from that one reaction element, though, this level is pretty easy. Also, I guess you could potentially farm for lives here if you wanted to (though the 60-second time limit almost makes that not worth it).
If you stomp a Cirno near the top of the level, you might score two hits on one, and that'll cause an actual koopa shell to show up!
Oh, and these dotted blocks are enemy-only blocks. They act as solid blocks for the enemies, but you'll just pass right through them.
And Sanae clears her first level! Sweet! Only 68 more levels to go... (I think there are a total of 70 levels in this hack...)
That was risky. I could've lost a shell there.
BGM: Castlevania: Dracula X - Map
According to TurnipEvernoteVirato, this says "Goji Kiyomi".

Wait a minute... I just realized there's a major glitch here! Why was that Cirno mission on level 7? It should totally have been on level 9! Wow, they really screwed that up. Totally a game-breaking glitch if you ask me. However, the game itself fortunately didn't crash, so I can still continue on to level 8 as planned.
(Also, I wonder if completing every single currently available level will unlock other levels too...)

When a level is completed, it'll be marked on the map, which is very nice, especially if you're doing the levels in any kind of "random" order! Also, you'll get a save prompt after each level. Also nice!
Huh. For some reason I can step onto empty spaces below the bottom row of levels, but those empty spaces aren't anything special, I don't think.
BGM: Super Mario Land - Birabuto Kingdom
Also, I'm going to do the upper part more carefully this time. I wouldn't want to lose a shell in some stupid way by accident.
Now, Goron50 and his pal, the Bear (MetalBenderJem) have been playing this hack recently, and I was interested in trying it, and I got a request to play it as well.
Argh! I let myself get burned! Well, there's my first death.
I wonder if there are any other additional maps with more levels, but I'll worry about that later. For right now, let's just go back and play level 5 like normal.
And that was totally unexpected! I thought the shell would go straight into the lava after hitting the block there!
...Hakurei Adventure whatever-that-says Mission Version 2 Reimu! But let's just call it "Hakurei Adventure Mission" to keep it simple.
Or, you could try doing the upper part of this room Bear's way! (Very risky, but man, did it look cool!)
Ah, but according to PeejsterM, this says: "Clear all of the missions! When everything is cleared, a path to the last boss will open!"
Miss just once, or let any of them fall into the lava, and the level becomes unwinnable. I hope you're good at midair catches!
Alright, Sanae, do you think you can take level 4?
Alright, so let's get this party started! Oh, and I'm going to actually go with 2 players this time just to show something (but I'll be controlling both of them myself).
Taking out that shell that way makes getting up easier. Then, the rest of this isn't too tough. Just carefully crush the remaining foes, and don't accidentally jump into a bullet.
Also, in addition to avoiding the flames, you have to be careful not to let any of the Remilia hats (shells) here go to waste.
Can Reimu succeed where Sanae failed?
Okay, next is level 5... Huh... That looks like a Yukari gap down there. Can I actually enter it?
Oh, cool! It's an extra map with nine additional levels! So I guess there are at least 79 levels in this hack, not just 70!
BGM: Mega Man X - Boomer Kuwanger's Stage
BGM: F-Zero - Mute City
Hey there duders, this is SomeGuy712x, and welcome to...
As long as you're not bouncing too crazily, this level isn't too difficult. Stomp every Cirno to clear the level.
Sweet! Sanae got one of her lost lives back!
Death BGM: SMB2 - Death

Okay, fortunately, the game didn't decide to say "screw you" this time, but if you're unlucky, a bullet could potentially surprise-blast you while you're near either edge of the room before you can react.
BGM: Breath of Fire - Lands Beyond the Ocean
Oh, sure. Now the shell goes straight into the lava the way I initially expected it to.
BGM: SMB1 - Castle Clear
Alright, so the levels can be played in any order, but I think I'll just start with the bottom-left corner, level 0, and work my way to the right from there.
So, next time, shall I resume with level 10 and continue doing these levels in a nice orderly fashion, or should I bounce around and do levels at random?
This one looks tricky, but honestly, this is one of the easier levels! (Insert evil laugh here!)
BGM: Final Fantasy 5 - Clash on the Big Bridge
Oh, and those clouds there are just part of the background, so don't get fooled into thinking that you can stand on them.

Uh, oh. If I had to guess, I'd say that the symbol on those blocks means "death", and they will kill you instantly if you touch them. Also, we're swimming here, and there are random bullets. Very tricky...
And, we're done! I thought for a split-second there that I was going to have to stomp that last enemy myself, but it just walked off into the lava for me.
Hopefully I won't be ambushed by a surprise bullet over here...

Hmm... Honestly, maybe I should stick to the orderly fashion, since Goron and Bear have been doing the levels pretty much randomly. Well, whatever I end up doing, we'll find out next time! To be continued...
This is another level where you have to defeat all of the enemies. That ON/OFF switch must be hit twice to do this, and you only get 2 potential shells, so be careful!
This hack does use a variety of custom music, so I'm going to try to identify every song that I know, and hope that you guys can fill in the blanks for me!
Wheeee!!! This is gonna be the whole video right here, folks. Nah, just kidding. (Huh, I wonder why level 39 is in the upper-left. Seems out of place...)
BGM: Ninja Gaiden NES - Act 5-3
Level 6...
BGM: Zelda: Twilight Princess - Secret Village

WHOOOAAA!!! Yeah, that's what'll happen if you touch the sides, and you probably won't be able to fully regain control if that happens, making it very likely you'll get killed (unless you've already stomped all the Cirnos).
Alright! That last bullet was maybe kind of close, but I had more than enough time to react to it.
Well, this level is obviously the strongest! Also, do not touch the sides of the level at all, or you'll just go bouncing crazily all over the place and probably get murdered!
Okay, so here's why I chose 2 players. The first player controls Reimu, and the second player plays as Sanae (but they're functionally identical in this hack, of course). So, now for level 1...
Yay, Reimu has completed the first level! (In most cases, don't worry about what your character will walk into during the victory march, but be warned-- Certain levels do contain Kaizo traps!)
Okay, now one more...

I guess Cirno wasn't expected to enter a "stunned shell" state, so those graphics weren't edited. Also, with each stomp counting towards the same combo, scoring a couple double-hits like that can make this a 1-up combo!
Awesome!
BGM: Mother - Bein' Friends
Level 3...
Well, Reimu, it's your turn. Let's see if you can avoid repeating Sanae's mistake.

Note: There seems to be a glitch involving the custom sprite that checks to see if all other enemy sprites are gone, and this causes the victory music to play its first few notes again as the screen fades out. It's nothing game-breaking, though.
Also, try to hang onto the first shell that comes at you so you can use it to take out the second shell.
Okay, so in each level, you have 60 game seconds to complete your mission. In this case, I've got to reach the goal sphere up there.
BGM: Final Fantasy 4 - Boss Battle
Next up is level 2. How tricky will this one be?
